Executive Profile
Hubert   de Pesquidoux  Executive Chairman, Mavenir SystemsAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships51--
Background

		Mr. Hubert de Pesquidoux serves as an Executive Partner and Partner at Siris Capital Group, LLC. Mr. de Pesquidoux serves as a Consultant of HDP Consulting. He advises several private companies in telecommunications and invests in private firms. He serves as an Executive Chairman at Xura, Inc. He has been an Executive Chairman of Premiere Global Services, Inc. Since November 2009 and also serves as its Executive Officer. He has been a Member of the Executive Advisory ... Board for Telmar Network Technology, Inc. since June 2009. He has over 20 years of experience of financial and operational management in the telecommunications industry. He has a deep and broad understanding of the all aspects of the high-tech sector: sales and marketing, research and development, finance, IT and supply chain. He served as the Manager of MIROR LLC. He served as the President of Alcatel-Lucent, S.A. since April 20, 2005 and also served as its Chief Financial Officer from October 2007 to November 2008, Chief Executive Officer of Enterprise Group/Head of Enterprise Group until November 2008 and Executive Vice President since April 2006. He worked at Alcatel and then Alcatel-Lucent, in the U.S., Canada and Europe. He was the President of the Enterprise Business Group. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Alcatel North America, a holding of Spatial Communications Technologies, Inc. until 2008 and also served as its Chief Financial Officer since 1998 and Chief Operating Officer from December 2002 to April 2006. He served as the President for the Plano-based unit at Alcatel-Lucent since April 20, 2005. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Alcatel USA. From 1991 to December 2008, he served various positions at the telecommunications company Alcatel-Lucent SA. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Alcatel-Lucent Canada Inc. since 2000 and also served as its Chief Operating Officer and President. He first joined Alcatel in 1991, holding the position of Corporate Treasurer for four years. Before joining Alcatel, he spent four years in investment banking, including two years in New York City. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of a CAC 40 / SEC registered company. He served as the Chairman of the Board at Tekelec, Inc. from May 2011 to January 2012. He served as the Chairman and Director of Alcatel-Lucent Canada Inc. He has been an Independent Director of RadiSys Corporation since April 11, 2012. He has been a Non-Employee Director at Criteo SA since October 2012. He is an Executive Chairman of Mavenir Systems. He has been a Director at Tekelec, Inc. since May 2009 and Sequans Communications S.A. since March 2011 and Premiere Global Services, Inc. since December 14, 2015. He serves as a Director for TNS, Telemar, Criteo Corp., and Radysis. He served as a Director of Thales SA and Alcatel-Lucent USA Inc. (Lucent Technologies Inc.). He served as a Director of Mavenir Systems, Inc. from January 30, 2012 to April 29, 2015. He was also elected Young Global Leader by the Economic World Forum. He has a long career in senior financial and operational management in the telecommunications industry. Mr. de Pesquidoux holds a Master's degree in Law from Nancy University, a Master's in Economics and Finance from the Institut d’Etudes Politiques de Paris, a DESS in International Affairs from Paris Dauphine and was a laureate in the “Concours Général de Droit”.Read Full Background




