Hubert de Pesquidoux
Former Chief Financial Officer, Alcatel-LucentFormer President, Alcatel-Lucent Enterprise
Hubert de Pesquidoux served as chief financial officer   of Alcatel-Lucent and president of the Enterprise business until  December 2008.  Prior to that position, Mr. de Pesquidoux was Alcatel’s  executive vice  president, president of Alcatel North America, and a  member of the Alcatel  Executive Committee. Previously, he was chief  operating officer of Alcatel North  America from 2002 to 2006 and chief  executive officer of Alcatel Canada starting  in 2000. In 1998, he  served as chief financial officer of Alcatel USA. Mr. de  Pesquidoux  first joined Alcatel in 1991 as corporate treasurer. 

Before joining   Alcatel, Mr. de Pesquidoux spent four years in the investment banking  industry.  Mr. Pesquidoux was recently named Chairman of Tekelec’s Board  of Directors on  which he has served as a Board Member since 2009. He  holds a master’s degree in  law and business from the Institute for  Political Studies (Sciences Po) in  Paris, as well as a DESS in finance  from Paris  Dauphine.

